00:45:21.530 --> 00:45:24.740
So the question is, do you tend
to just write linearly or do

00:45:24.740 --> 00:45:26.120
you jump around?

00:45:26.120 --> 00:45:28.540
I think it varies by writer.

00:45:28.540 --> 00:45:30.120
I tend to write
from the beginning

00:45:30.120 --> 00:45:32.650
and through to the
end, but I do find

00:45:32.650 --> 00:45:34.920
that if I'm getting
into this middle part,

00:45:34.920 --> 00:45:37.310
and the month is kind of
starting to get away from me,

00:45:37.310 --> 00:45:38.540
I will skip ahead.

00:45:38.540 --> 00:45:40.790
And it's just so much
easier to revise, I think,

00:45:40.790 --> 00:45:43.197
when you do you have
all those parts,

00:45:43.197 --> 00:45:44.530
and you're just doing an infill.

00:45:44.530 --> 00:45:46.735
So I would say
whatever works for you.

00:45:46.735 --> 00:45:48.360
