momentum is so important.

00:46:11.904 --> 00:46:14.744
And really, whatever it takes
to keep you moving forward

00:46:14.744 --> 00:46:15.410
with that story.

00:46:15.410 --> 00:46:17.419
It's all about making
decisions, and that's

00:46:17.419 --> 00:46:19.210
the hardest thing with
a novel, because you

00:46:19.210 --> 00:46:20.110
want to wreck it, right?

00:46:20.110 --> 00:46:21.734
You're like, oh this
is so good so far,

00:46:21.734 --> 00:46:23.244
I don't want to
make a bad decision

00:46:23.244 --> 00:46:24.660
and take it in
this bad direction.

00:46:24.660 --> 00:46:26.350
But the truth is,
there are really

00:46:26.350 --> 00:46:27.910
no wrong directions
in a first draft.

00:46:27.910 --> 00:46:29.890
Just make the decision,
go, you can always

00:46:29.890 --> 00:46:31.410
go back and change it.

